You can do that like I said by keeping a reference to the `Provide<List<Header>>` that you give to the `RestAdapter` and then returning a different set of headers based on the logged in/our state.

For simplicity, I'll change it tonight to be:

``` java
interface Headers {
  List<Header> get();
}
```

â€¦so it's less awkward than using a provider directly, easier to make a `@Singleton`, and able to be implemented by any existing class you have which may deal with things like user state.

Not sure about the implementation. Maybe it's not a easy to generalize and at the moment I've extended ApacheClient

``` java
